thread.title_full: Delia survives, Mohd Nafiizwan crashes out in 2015 US Open Squash Championships

title: Delia survives, Mohd Nafiizwan crashes out in 2015 US Open Squash Championships
text:
Delia survives, Mohd Nafiizwan crashes out in 2015 US Open Squash Championships Sunday October 11, 2015 Print Article 
India’s Alankamony Anaka (right) returns a shot against Malaysia’s Delia Odette Arnold (left) during the squash team final round at the 2014 Asian Games in Incheon, September 27, 2014. — AFP pic KUALA LUMPUR, Oct 11 — Malaysian number two Delia Arnold got off to a perfect start in the 2015 United States Squash Championships by moving into the second round of the tournament held in Philadelphia, United States. 
In the opening match today, Delia, the 11th seed only took 29 minutes to sweep aside unheralded Nicolette Fernandes of Guyana, 11-3,11-3, 11-6. 
Delia who is vying for her first victory of the season, however, faces a mammoth task against France’s world number four, Camille Serme in the second round tomorrow. 
Camille who received stiff resistance from Olivia Blatchford from the host country emerged with a 8-11, 11-3, 11-5, 11-6 victory in another opening match, the tournament website;www.usopensquash.com reported. 
Malaysian squash queen and defending champion, Datuk Nicol David is slated to play against Hong Kong qualifier, Joey Chan in her opening encounter, late today. 
Meanwhile, it was the end of the road for Malaysia’s sole representative in the men’s category as Mohd Nafiizwan Adnan was eliminated after losing 9-11, 3-11, 7-11 to fifth seed and former three-time world champion Ramy Ashour from Egypt in the opening tie on Sunday. — Bernama
